Reasoning: The paper discusses the design of rational agents and their decision-making processes, which are central topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of possible-worlds models and decision trees for representing and reasoning about beliefs, goals, intentions, time, actions, probabilities, and payoffs suggests that the paper may also belong to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper's focus on decision-making and planning aligns with the machine learning (cs.ML) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
